{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Meringue","content":["Preheat oven to 140°C. Line two baking trays with baking paper. On the baking paper, draw three evenly-sized circles (Ø 20 cm) with a pencil (you should fit two circles on one sheet, and the remaining circle on the other).","Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in sugar, then set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk <\/strong>into very clean mixing bowl (see Tip). Place egg whites into mixing bowl and whisk <nobr>2 min 30 sec - 3 min\/speed 3<\/nobr> or until stiff peaks form.","With blades turning at <nobr>speed 3<\/nobr> slowly add sugar until all incorporated. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","Add vinegar and sifted cocoa then gently fold in using spatula.","Spread mixture over the three circles on baking paper and bake for 45 minutes - 1 hour (140°C) until set. Turn off oven and leave meringues inside to cool completely (ideally overnight)."]},{"title":"Crème Pâtissière","content":["Place chocolate in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then melt <nobr>4 min\/37°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Scrape down and melt again <nobr>1 min\/37°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and keep warm. Clean mixing bowl.","Place flour, cocoa, sugar, milk, cream, eggs and egg yolks in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>7 min\/90°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add vanilla and reserved melted chocolate  then mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Pour into a bowl, cover with damp greaseproof paper and set aside to cool."]},{"title":"Assembly","content":["To assemble, take a meringue circle and spread with a third of the crème pâtissière. Place another meringue circle on top and repeat, building layers to finish with a layer of crème pâtissière.","Serve decorated with chocolate mini eggs."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Meringue","content":["6 large eggs, separated","300 g golden caster sugar","1 tsp red wine vinegar","3 Tbsp cocoa powder, sifted"]},{"title":"Crème Pâtissière","content":["100 g dark chocolate, pieces or callets","2 Tbsp plain flour","2 Tbsp cocoa powder","100 g golden caster sugar","200 g whole milk","300 g double cream","2 large eggs","2 egg yolks, from large eggs","1 tsp vanilla extract"]},{"title":"Decoration","content":["mini chocolate eggs"]}],"id":"r88334","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-xEwPOa_7izg\/XZankxk3gwI\/AAAAAAAAhBI\/mLn_5_VMuQ8KFiMlb_99jrUdSIazfbsaACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_NBdNrOvt1n0pkHw4.png","title":"Chocolate Meringue Stack","publishedAt":"2016-02-29T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"12.5 g","fat":"35.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"60.8 g","calories":"2567 kJ \/ 614 kcal"},"usefulItems":"pencil, 2 baking trays and baking paper, bowl, greaseproof paper, oven","hintsAndTricks":["The meringues and crème pâtissière can be made ahead and then assembled just before serving.","A grease-free mixing bowl and whisk are essential for well-formed meringues.","If your baking trays are very small, you may need to use three to fit all the meringue discs."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","7h 30m","8 portions"]}